---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'

const images = [
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/01-the-horde-wall-of-radiant-fire.png",
    "title": "The Horde — Wall of Radiant Fire",
    "caption": "An aasimar sorcerer standing on the underside of a massive floating stone citadel — gravity inverted, the city's architecture hanging above like a ceiling. Before him, a towering 60-foot wall of blazing white-gold radiant fire stretches across a stone expanse."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/02-virgil-s-charge-the-agent-smith-scene.png",
    "title": "Virgil's Charge — The Agent Smith Scene",
    "caption": "A massive goliath barbarian in giant form, easily nine feet tall, sprinting through an ocean of ghouls. Bodies fly in every direction like bowling pins — some launched airborne, others trampled flat."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/03-toven-s-sunbeam-debut-the-matrix-motorcycle.png",
    "title": "Toven's Sunbeam Debut — The Matrix Motorcycle",
    "caption": "A druid channeling a 60-foot beam of concentrated sunlight from outstretched hands, sweeping it horizontally through a cavern filled with hundreds of ghouls. The beam cuts a clean line through the darkness, ghouls disintegrating into ash and dust where the light touches them."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/04-sundr-rides-the-golden-dragon.png",
    "title": "Sundr Rides the Golden Dragon",
    "caption": "An aasimar sorcerer astride a shimmering translucent gold dragon spirit, soaring over an endless sea of ghouls on the underside of a floating citadel. The dragon is large, spectral, radiating golden light — more spirit than flesh."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/05-chain-lightning-innate-sorcery.png",
    "title": "Chain Lightning — Innate Sorcery",
    "caption": "An aasimar sorcerer on dragonback, arms outstretched, unleashing a massive arc of transmuted radiant chain lightning. The bolt — blazing white-gold instead of blue — strikes a ghoulish humanoid figure (Nakhorus) dead center, then forks outward into a dozen secondary arcs that chain through surrounding ghouls."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/06-kiet-decapitates-nakhorus.png",
    "title": "Kiet Decapitates Nakhorus",
    "caption": "A dragonborn fighter mid-swing, scimitars crossing in a scissor-cut through the neck of a gaunt, burned humanoid figure. Nakhorus's mouth is open — mid-sentence, mid-monologue — as his head separates from his body."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/07-virgil-s-trophy-predator.png",
    "title": "Virgil's Trophy — Predator",
    "caption": "A goliath barbarian holding up the jaw of a ghoulish humanoid, ripped clean off the skull, in a triumphant pose. The body of Nakhorus lies crumpled at his feet."
  },
  {
    "src": "/studio/session-109/08-the-leaderless-army.png",
    "title": "The Leaderless Army",
    "caption": "Wide shot from behind five exhausted adventurers — one on dragonback, one on a mammoth, one on a flying carpet — hovering above the underside of a floating citadel. Stretching beneath them: four hundred ghouls that have stopped moving."
  }
]
---

<Layout title="Session 109 — Tales of the Radiant Citadel" description="Picking up from session 108's cliffhanger, the party engaged Nakhorus and his army of 400+ ghouls on the underside of the Radiant Citadel. Sam introduced h">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <a href="/studio" class="text-sm text-earth hover:text-ink transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">&larr; Studio</a>

    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-2">
      Session 109
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth mb-1">Tales of the Radiant Citadel &middot; March 3, 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mb-8">Post-Arc 8 — Crimson Rasp / Citadel Underworld</p>

    <div class="prose-section text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-12 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Picking up from session 108's cliffhanger, the party engaged Nakhorus and his army of 400+ ghouls on the underside of the Radiant Citadel. Sam introduced horde mechanics — damage overflows, AoE multiplied 4x, and a clock to track the hunt for Nakhorus. Sundr's transmuted Wall of Fire (radiant) blocked the north quadrant. Toven dropped toad form to debut Sunbeam, then owl-scouted from above. Virgil activated giant form and bulldozed through the horde like Agent Smith clones. Sundr summoned a gold draconic spirit, rode it south, and landed Chain Lightning (transmuted to radiant) on Nakhorus — 52 damage, leaving him at 3 HP. The difference: Innate Sorcery boosted the DC by 1, and Nakhorus failed his save by exactly 1. Kiet dashed in and decapitated him mid-monologue. The ghouls immediately became listless. The party looted Nakhorus's papers (Virgil ripped his jaw off, Predator-style), recovered a ceremonial Shield Bearer sword, and flew out. Back topside, they debriefed with Xolace, long-rested, and read the battle plans — revealing a dual-army strategy: ghouls from the dead, Helmed Horrors from extracted souls by a woman in a black veil. Next stop: God's Breath, where Grand Palvo and the sphinx Apoxus await.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Highlights</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light leading-relaxed space-y-2 mb-12 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sam's Horde Mechanics</strong> — Sam divided the ghoul army into four quadrants — North, South, East, West</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Round 1: Establishing Defenses</strong> — **Haru** investigated for Nakhorus at disadvantage (ground level), rolled 15 — worth two slices on the clock. Used bonus action to cast **Divine Favor**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Horde Strikes Back</strong> — Everyone on the ground made **Dex saves** (with Haru's +5 aura) against 8d6 horde damage</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Round 2: Virgil Spots Nakhorus</strong> — **Haru** searched again — rolled **24**, filled more clock slices. Sam narrowed it down: &quot;He's gotta be somewhere to the top&quot; — confirmed **south**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr Summons the Dragon</strong> — **Sundr cast Summon Draconic Spirit** (5th level) — dropped Wall of Fire concentration (but not before rolling one last round of wall damage: 5d8 x4)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet's Failed Haru Grab</strong> — **Kiet** flew up and dashed to close distance. Tried to grab Haru to carry him — **failed the athletics check**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Toven's Sunbeam Snipe + Hidden Step</strong> — **Toven (owl form)** flew within range and fired **Sunbeam** directly at Nakhorus. Nakhorus has **magical resistance** (advantage on saves) but still took 17 damage</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Dragon Shield</strong> — Gasts targeted Sundr — all missed. Dragon grants **+4 AC** (total 21)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Haru Summons his Steed</strong> — **Haru** burned a 4th-level slot to **summon his steed** (mammoth, flying), mounted up, and started catching up to the group</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Round 3: The Kill</strong> — **Virgil** double-moved (move + dash action) — giant form speed 45, doubled to 90 with dash. Arrived adjacent to Nakhorus but had no attack action left</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr's Chain Lightning — THE Moment</strong> — Erik: &quot;I wanna fly within range of chain lightning, and we're gonna blast this guy.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet Delivers the Killing Blow</strong> — **Kiet** dashed to close the remaining 60 feet (move + action surge) — ended adjacent to Nakhorus</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Army Goes Dark</strong> — Sam: &quot;The ghouls are becoming listless and undirected... they're probably not going to be an effective army and storm the Radiant Citadel. But they're still gonna damage you every turn if you're sticking around here, because there's still a horde of hungry ghouls. It's just nothing's directing them anymore.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Looting Nakhorus (Predator-Style)</strong> — Virgil looted the body — then ripped off Nakhorus's jaw. &quot;Like, predator style.&quot; Sam: &quot;It comes off with a satisfying crack.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Fancy Sword</strong> — Toven (owl form, perception check) spotted a **fancy sword** half-buried in refuse on the underside</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Escape Flight</strong> — Coordinated exit: Toven's mammoth carried Virgil (who shrunk from giant form), Sundr rode the summoned dragon, Kiet and Haru on the flying carpet</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Return to the Preserve of Ancestors</strong> — Glorb at the door: &quot;Woah, you people look awful. Look like you could use a nice bath.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Debriefing Xolace</strong> — Xolace rushed over: &quot;What news?&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Intelligence from Nakhorus's Papers</strong> — </li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Crimson Rasp Status</strong> — Erik: &quot;Sam, can we see the lieutenant's map with another x on the board?&quot; — Sam x'd out Nakhorus</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Sphere Regret</strong> — Someone mentioned the sphere of annihilation: &quot;There is a world in which you had a sphere of annihilation down here.&quot;</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Art</h2>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      {images.map((img) => (
        <figure>
          <img
            src={img.src}
            alt={img.title}
            class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-lg"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-3">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink text-sm">{img.title}</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mt-1">{img.caption}</p>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-cream-dark mt-16 pt-8">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3">Party</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Sundr</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Erik) — Aasimar Sorcerer</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Kiet</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Jonas) — Dragonborn Fighter</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Virgil</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Kyle) — Goliath Barbarian</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Toven</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Max) — Druid</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Haru</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Hunterleigh) — Kobold Paladin</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">—</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Sam (DM))</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
